This file contains a python file the groq api key can be found in "https://console.groq.com/keys"
Steps to be followed before running the python file and installation for the code requirement:
1. Install Python

Download Python (3.10+ recommended):
Python Official Website

During installation → ✔ Add Python to PATH

2. Install VS Code Extensions

Open VS Code → Extensions (Ctrl+Shift+X) → install:

Python Extension (Microsoft)
Pylance
3. Open Terminal in VS Code

Run:

pip install flask
pip install flask-mail
pip install flask-cors
pip install openai
pip install pdfplumber
pip install python-docx
pip install werkzeug

Or install all together:

pip install flask flask-mail flask-cors openai pdfplumber python-docx werkzeug
4. (Recommended) Create requirements.txt

Create a file:

flask
flask-mail
flask-cors
openai
pdfplumber
python-docx
werkzeug

Then install:

pip install -r requirements.txt
5. Run the project
python "Pasted code(2).py"

Your Flask server should start:

Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000

In the python file add the key in the api key section of the code and run the code and open  http://127.0.0.1:5000
